.TH SINGINE-TRANSFER 1 "2026-03-13" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-transfer \- file transfer, queues, stacks, and XML processing helpers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine transfer
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B transfer
command groups operational helpers for moving files, invoking SSH and SFTP,
maintaining simple persistent queues and stacks, and processing XML or JSON
request/response payloads.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B sync
Sync files via rsync or scp.
.TP
.B ssh
Run a command over SSH.
.TP
.B sftp
Upload or download a file over SFTP.
.TP
.B queue
Persistent FIFO queue operations.
.TP
.B stack
Persistent LIFO stack operations.
.TP
.B structure
Inspect the structure of a queue, stack, or JSON state.
.TP
.B process-request
Parse an XML request into a structured envelope.
.TP
.B generate-response
Generate response variants from input.
.TP
.B project
Project selected fields from JSON input.
.TP
.B analyze-result
Compute a basic summary for a JSON result.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine transfer queue push item-a
singine transfer queue list
singine transfer stack push item-a
singine transfer ssh host.example.org --cmd "hostname"
singine transfer process-request --xml request.xml
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1)
